node.text:
I'm Stoked to introduce my new Signature Edition Certified Sweatsaver Helmet from @triple8nyc—featuring, a crisp, matte Satin Metallic finish, and lightning-bolt graphics. Available Now!

* Dual Certified: Complies with U.S. CPSC Safety Standard for Bicycle Helmets for Persons Age 5 and Older and ASTM F-1492 Skate safety standards.
* Includes 2 sets of Sweatsaver liners to customize fit
* A portion of sales will be donated to @theskateparkproject (formerly The Tony Hawk Foundation) to continue its mission of empowering youth through the creation of public skateparks in low-income communities.

node.text:
GSD invented the Boneless. The Gonz mastered it on the streets, Steve Cab and Jeff Phillips owned it on vert. All I did was keep doing them, and I’m still doing them, and I’m not stopping. The only thing new happening here is my Signature Certified Sweatsaver Helmet from @triple8nyc, Available Now! Thanks for Your Support!

Photo: @derk_bertz

node.text:
Introducing @streetplantbeer!

My Family and I are excited to join the passionate craft beer community here in Central Iowa. Our first offering is a Refreshing and Crushable American Wheat Craft Beer, brewed independently at @carrollbrewing for Iowa’s patios, backyards, and driveways, or wherever people come together to celebrate and share good times. Much Love and Thanks to the crew at Carroll Brewing for helping to make this dream a reality! Cheers!

If you live in Central Iowa, ask your local retailer, bar, or restaurant to carry Street Plant. Available through @dolldistributing_dsm.

Art: @jakeearp
Photo: @mddkm

node.text:
SINCE WE WERE KIDS!

We grew up in the same neighborhood, listening to the same records, and we have been playing in this band together since 1981. Eli joined us upon his birth in 1985. Now we’re back with our first shows in a few years! Our 2021 Summer Tour kicks off this Sunday in Cumming, Iowa. We’ll see you there! FUCK YEAH!

node.text:
GROW YOUNG AGAIN

The sand ran out on yesterday; it was over. Everything I knew and had done since I was sixteen came to an abrupt end. But instead of growing up in that moment, I grew young again. And with the same Intensity, Passion, and Creativity I put into my Skating when I was a teenager, I put into my Skateboard Company, @streetplant, when I was forty-five. 

With the Love and Support of my Family, I started writing a new story—one without the impersonal demands of sponsors. Still, I continued to work with @triple8nyc to promote helmet use in Skateboarding. Not because they paid me to wear a helmet, but because I chose to wear a helmet, and they Supported me in that choice. Being free of other sponsors allowed me to put the helmet on and keep it on. And the good folks at @socco78 stuck it out with me as well, with no pressure at all. And six years went by in the blink of an eye.

Then @cariumaskateboarding called. A call I never expected and had given up on thinking was a possibility ever again. I genuinely thought that time in my Skateboard Life was over, and I was at peace with it. But what I've learned is that when you stop pursuing, things ensue and happen in their own time. And now, to be representing @cariuma, a company I revere for their Principles and Values, and to be on a team with the very best up and coming young Skaters in the world is Soul-Satisfying. And then to also have a Signature Shoe in development with such a Forward-Thinking company making the very best Skate Shoes—what more can I say? I'm Beyond Stoked. And at fifty-one, I can Appreciate this season more so than any other time in my Skateboard Life. 

All this to say THANK YOU to Cariuma, Triple 8, Socco, and @violentgentlemen for Believing in me and Supporting me in my Skating and my other endeavors. I count my Blessings daily. Much Love!
